&lt;h3&gt;Overview of the Firm&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FGS Global helps the world&#39;s most influential leaders move minds and markets. Working where business, government, and public opinion intersect, we advise CEOs, boards, and leadership teams at the most consequential moments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work as one team across geographies and disciplines - bringing together specialists with backgrounds in communications, finance, law, government, journalism, data science, and digital. Whatever the moment demands, we combine multidimensional perspectives to help leaders anticipate what&#39;s next, engage the stakeholders who matter, and drive meaningful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Across 31 global offices, we draw on the full depth of the firm so clients can operate with clarity, act with confidence, and lead with trust. This collaborative approach has established FGS as a market leader: we are consistently ranked Band 1 for Crisis &amp;amp; Risk Management and Litigation Support by Chambers and Partners, and were ranked the #1 Global M&amp;amp;A PR firm by deal value and deal count for four consecutive years (Mergermarket, 2025).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Associate will play a critical role in delivering high-quality equity advisory and investor relations counsel to clients across Asia and be part of a fast-growing Investor Relations advisory team in Singapore. This position requires a unique combination of deep financial literacy, strategic advisory expertise, and the ability to operate independently in high-stakes capital markets situations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have demonstrated experience in investment banking (ECM or M&amp;amp;A) or sell-side equity research. This role is designed for individuals who can bridge technical financial analysis with strategic storytelling to help clients navigate complex investor relations, capital markets transactions, and corporate positioning challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Candidates with less experience will be considered as Associate.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key day-to-day client contact, managing accounts and overseeing project delivery across IR and equity advisory mandates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate internal teams and external stakeholders to ensure timely, high-quality execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead preparation of investor-facing materials including earnings presentations, roadshow decks, investor day content, and Q&amp;amp;A documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop data-driven equity narratives that articulate clients&#39; investment cases, growth strategies, and competitive positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft meeting briefs, key messages, and speaker notes for client engagements with institutional investors and sell-side analysts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support clients through capital markets transactions including IPOs, equity raises, and M&amp;amp;A announcements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and analyze share price movements, trading activity, institutional ownership trends, and analyst consensus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct peer benchmarking, valuation analysis, earnings reviews, and market sentiment tracking to inform client strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare internal and client-facing reports synthesizing financial data, investor feedback, and market developments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with institutional investors, sell-side analysts, and other capital markets stakeholders across Southeast Asia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather market intelligence and investor feedback to inform FGS counsel and client positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mentor Associates on day-to-day projects; provide regular coaching and feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to new business pitches, proposals, and cross-selling opportunities with existing clients.&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FGS Global is the world’s leading stakeholder strategy firm, with approximately 1,400 professionals around the world, advising clients in navigating critical issues and reputational challenges. FGS was formed from the combination of Finsbury, The Glover Park Group, Hering Schuppener and Sard Verbinnen &amp;amp; Co to offer board-level and C-suite counsel in all aspects of stakeholder strategy — including corporate reputation, crisis management, and public affairs and is also the leading force in transaction and financial communications worldwide.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Transaction &amp;amp; Financial Communications practice sits at the heart of the most consequential moments in corporate life. When companies go public, pursue a major acquisition, face an activist investor, or navigate a complex restructuring, they turn to us. We help them shape their story, engage the right stakeholders, and communicate with clarity to investors, to the market, and to the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a team of close to 50 consultants across our offices in The Hague and Amsterdam, we are always looking for talented individuals who are eager to advance their careers and contribute to the success of our clients and the growth of our firm. Our work is fast-paced and exciting: you will work on exchange-listed transactions and high-profile M&amp;amp;A deals, advise companies on their strategic positioning, and help build the stakeholder and media relationships that make transactions succeed. If you have a background in communications, journalism, consulting, investor relations or finance, thrive under pressure, and want to work alongside colleagues across our global network on complex, consequential mandates, we’d like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Does this sound like you? Then we look forward to your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us&amp;nbsp;as:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Associate Transaction &amp;amp; Financial Communications in Amsterdam&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What tasks can you look forward to?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From day one, you will work together with our project teams on various strategic communication topics for national and international clients, especially in the context of M&amp;amp;A transactions, IPOs and strategic realignments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will support our team in developing measures for the strategic positioning of companies and company boards as well as advising our clients on building strategic stakeholder relations including media.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You build strong business relationships and inspire local and global stakeholders to achieve high-quality results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You actively drive new ideas and innovative communication formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will create documents for internal and external communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will also be responsible for supporting our team in client acquisition and the further development of existing mandates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What should you bring along?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have successfully completed your university studies with very good results - the subject area is less important than your enthusiasm for communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have several years of relevant professional experience in journalism, communications, consulting, investor relations and/or other areas of the financial sector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate fluently in Dutch and very well in English – ideally, you have also spent time abroad in an English-speaking country.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a high level of text competence and strong communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a good economic and political understanding, sound judgment, a high level

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FGS Global is seeking a detail-oriented and highly organized Staff Accountant to support the North America Accounting and Finance team. This role will assist with monthly accounting activities, transaction review, account reconciliations, journal entries, and close deliverables across the region and its business units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Staff Accountant will work closely with members of the North America finance team and cross-functional partners to help ensure financial transactions are accurate, complete, properly supported, and recorded in accordance with U.S. GAAP and FGS Global’s internal accounting policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role has the option to be remote if not located near one of the firm&#39;s existing offices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the North America team with the monthly, quarterly, and annual close process, including preparation of journal entries, account reconciliations, supporting schedules, and other close deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the accuracy, completeness, and integrity of financial data across the region and its business units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare routine journal entries and assist with recurring monthly accounting activities, including accruals, reclasses, prepaid expenses, fixed assets, and other assigned areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare account reconciliations and supporting schedules in a timely manner, researching and resolving reconciling items as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review accounts payable transactions, including vendor bills, employee expense reports, corporate card activity, and related supporting documentation for accuracy, completeness, coding, approvals, and compliance with internal policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with transactional accounting work, including invoice review, expense report review, vendor and payment support, data entry, account coding, and follow-up on missing or incomplete documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the preparation of financial reports and internal reporting schedules, ensuring information is complete, accurate, and aligned with internal accounting policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compliance with regulatory requirements and assist in preparing documentation and analysis for external audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain and improve accounting processes, documentation, and internal controls to support timely and accurate reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with North America finance teams to gather required financial data, promote consistency in reporting practices, and support adherence to close timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
